channel.title: Need help badly!
channel.description:
So im in the process of making my RSPS and im trying to compile my source but it keeps saying this: [url=http://gyazo.com/8da04816deb180053a4543fcd029538e]http://gyazo.com/8da04816deb180053a4543fcd029538e[/url] I have no idea what to do, I have JDK 1.7.0_? and JRE7
Please help me. Im new to this too so please dont act like im supposed to know what i am doing.

item.title: Need help badly!
item.dc:creator: @RandQm RandQm
item.description:
@RandQm wrote:

[quote=“Daginith, post:5, topic:438496”][quote author=xXThatOneSkaterKidXx link=topic=541213.msg3964342#msg3964342 date=1333570779]
Easy fix.
Right click the Compiler and click edit.
Change your java to any of your jdks.
Version “jdk1.6.0_31” is what I recommend.
It’s the best possible jdk for clients.

Also, you can’t use compilers with jre, hence the error.
must be a jdk.
[/quote]
Why do you recommend 1.6_u31?[/quote]

Read full topic
